How to use dmscanlib:
-----------------

  Decoding Images
  ====================================
  1. Scan the bottom of a pallet at 300, 400, or 600 dpi.

  2. Save the file as a BMP. (eg. pallet.bmp)

  3. Extract and run dmscanlib.exe with the following arguments:
  	./dmscanlib.exe -p 1 -d -i pallet.bmp

  4. A file dmscanlib.txt will be created, it will contain the barccodes of each test tube successfully decoded.

  5. Debugging files that will be created include: blobRegions.bmp, decoded.bmp, filtered.bmp.

  6. For additional command line arguments: ./dmscanlib.exe --help

REQUIRED PACKAGES ON UBUNTU

  - libdmtx-dev
  - libopenthreads-dev
  - libgoogle-glog-dev
  - libgtest-dev

  The image information generator tool requires the following package:

    - libgflags-dev


JNI

  The JNI class used to interface to the dmscanlib is ScanLibImpl. To generate 
  the C header file use the following commands:

   - cd to <scannerConfig_proj>/bin
   - javah -jni edu.ualberta.med.scannerconfig.dmscanlib.ScanLib
   - mv edu_ualberta_med_scannerconfig_dmscanlib_ScanLib.h
     <dmscanlib_proj/src.
     
GTEST
    sudo apt-get install cmake 
    cd /usr/src/gtest
    sudo cmake .
    sudo make
    # copy or symlink libgtest.a and libgtest_main.a to your /usr/lib folder
    sudo mv libg* /usr/lib/

    use --gtest_filter=* to run a single test


VALGRIND

  Use the following commands to check for memory leaks:

  valgrind --track-origins=yes --tool=memcheck --leak-check=yes -v \
    --show-reachable=yes --num-callers=10 Linux-Debug/dmscanlib 
